(thirdQuint)Cetuximab in Treating Patients With Mntrier Disease at High Risk of Developing Stomach Cancer.

 OBJECTIVES: - Evaluate clinical and biochemical parameter response in patients with Menetrier disease at high risk of developing gastric cancer treated with cetuximab.

 OUTLINE: This is a non-randomized study.

 Patients receive cetuximab IV on days 1, 8, 15, and 22.

 Treatment repeats every 4 weeks in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

 Patients complete a quality of life questionnaire at baseline and during week 4.

 PROJECTED ACCRUAL: A total of 10 patients will be accrued for this study.

