RATIONALE: Monoclonal antibodies, such as cetuximab, can block tumor growth in different ways.

 Some block the ability of tumor cells to grow and spread.

 Others find tumor cells and help kill them or carry tumor-killing substances to them.

 PURPOSE: This clinical trial is studying how well cetuximab works in treating patients with Menetrier disease at high risk of developing stomach cancer.

